## Knowledge Base Rules (Optional — LLM-Wiki Pattern)

If your repo uses the `knowledge/` directory:

```
knowledge/
├── raw/         ← immutable source layer (user curates, agent reads only)
└── wiki/        ← agent-owned synthesis layer
    ├── index.md       (catalog of all pages)
    ├── log.md         (append-only chronology)
    ├── _template.md   (required page shape)
    └── *.md           (concept/entity pages)
```

### Rules
1. **Raw is immutable.** Never modify `knowledge/raw/`.
2. **Wiki is yours to own.** Create pages, update them, maintain cross-references.
3. **Cross-linking is mandatory.** Every non-stub page links to ≥2 other pages.
4. **Always update `knowledge/wiki/index.md`** when creating/removing pages.
5. **Always append to `knowledge/wiki/log.md`** with format: `## [YYYY-MM-DD] action | subject → pages touched`

